Package hr.caellian.flow.data

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Flux<S extends FluxType>
    Flux is a representation of transferable unit.
    FluxType<B extends Flux>
    Flux Types are used to differentiate and construct different types of Flux objects.
    PropertyManager
    Property Manager is an interface marking a class capable of containing Properties in a form of a map.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    FluxGroup
    Flux Groups are a simple way of categorising different Flux Types which helps with Flux conversion.
    Pair<A,B>
    Container for value pairs.
    Property<T>
    Property is data wrapper which makes Flux data manipulation a bit easier and predictable.
